1
00:00:01,835 --> 00:00:04,171
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:29,590
[Near] The Second L,
and the person I think is Kira,

3
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:31,258
can only be one man.

4
00:01:31,383 --> 00:01:32,259
Light Yagami.

5
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:34,678
This is Kiyomi Takada from News 6.

6
00:01:34,886 --> 00:01:37,222
I have an announcement
that comes directly from Kira.

7
00:01:37,306 --> 00:01:39,474
His words are to become
the new law of the world.

8
00:01:39,683 --> 00:01:41,143
I've just had an idea.

9
00:01:41,643 --> 00:01:43,937
I think we can make use
of Kiyomi Takada.

10
00:01:45,063 --> 00:01:46,315
Please excuse me.

11
00:01:46,982 --> 00:01:47,899
[gasps] Kira...

12
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:51,320
-[Matsuda] He's removing the bugs?
-We don't have a choice.

13
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,071
Listen, Kiyomi…

14
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:55,073
I am the real Kira.

15
00:01:55,282 --> 00:01:56,325
[gasps]

16
00:01:57,409 --> 00:01:59,786
Light is... Kira?

17
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:02,831
SCORN

18
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,835
[Near] All the pieces
have fallen into place.

19
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:09,713
Now that things have come this far,

20
00:02:09,921 --> 00:02:11,673
it's my turn to go to Japan.

21
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:14,885
Commander Rester?

22
00:02:15,177 --> 00:02:16,053
Yes.

23
00:02:16,136 --> 00:02:18,889
I'm afraid I need you
to return to New York immediately.

24
00:02:19,014 --> 00:02:20,057
Right now?

25
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:21,808
Yes, I'm intending to go to Japan.

26
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:25,312
Alright. So you would like me
to stay in New York while you're gone?

27
00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:26,688
Not at all.

28
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:28,899
Then what's the point of me
coming back there?

29
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:32,194
Truth is, I've never made
travel arrangements

30
00:02:32,277 --> 00:02:33,945
or boarded a flight on my own before.

31
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:37,658
That's why I need you to come back,
so you can escort me.

32
00:02:37,949 --> 00:02:38,867
Understood.

33
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:42,537
[plane engines roaring]

34
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:49,419
[Matsuda] We got 'em!

35
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:52,381
Both Yoshida Productions and NHN
are practically begging us now.

36
00:02:52,506 --> 00:02:55,467
The Great Misa-Misa Comeback Plan
was a huge success!

37
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:59,221
These days, it's nearly impossible
for anyone to get into NHN,

38
00:02:59,346 --> 00:03:01,348
but this will get us full access.

39
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:02,599
Yeah, that's right.

40
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,893
Mogi will be gaining entry
as Misa's manager.

41
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,770
It'll definitely be to our advantage

42
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:08,980
to have someone
who can go in and out freely.

43
00:03:09,064 --> 00:03:11,441
In the meantime,
I'll continue investigating Takada.

44
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:13,360
-[beeping]
-[all] Hmm?

45
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:15,696
This is Near. I want to speak to L.

46
00:03:16,029 --> 00:03:18,448
This is L. What is it you want from us?

47
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:22,035
I'm following through with my goal
to arrest Kira.

48
00:03:22,244 --> 00:03:24,371
And that's why I'm in Japan now.

49
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:26,164
He's in Japan?

50
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:27,457
Why tell me?

51
00:03:27,624 --> 00:03:28,875
He's up to something.

52
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:32,170
[Near] L, I presume
you've already contacted Takada

53
00:03:32,254 --> 00:03:34,256
for the purposes
of your own investigation?

54
00:03:34,423 --> 00:03:35,298
[men] Huh?

55
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:38,635
That's right. In fact, I'm investigating
her myself at the moment.

56
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,137
I see.

57
00:03:40,512 --> 00:03:41,513
For the time being,

58
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,224
it's a given that if we want
to get any closer to capturing Kira,

59
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:47,602
we'll have to keep an eye on
Kiyomi Takada and NHN in general.

60
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:50,897
I want you to pass on a message.

61
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,441
Inform her that as of now,

62
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:56,278
several SPK members have entered Japan
in order to catch and arrest Kira.

63
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:58,321
Huh? But why do that?

64
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:00,907
To lure Kira out of hiding.

65
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:02,367
[all gasping]

66
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:04,578
[Near] I also want you to mention
the following to her,

67
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:05,954
so she'll relay it to Kira.

68
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:09,040
In total, there are only four
active members of the SPK.

69
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,292
That includes myself.

70
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:13,670
Kira won't be able to resist
such an opportunity.

71
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,213
Knowing him, he won't run.

72
00:04:15,297 --> 00:04:17,799
Instead, he'll try to kill us
before we get too close.

73
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:19,801
That's where I'll beat him
at his own game.

74
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:21,887
[Light] Beat me at my own game, huh?

75
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:24,055
[tense music playing]

76
00:04:25,223 --> 00:04:26,349
Alright, Near.

77
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:29,478
If that's how you want it,
I'll accept your challenge.

78
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:32,022
I am in Japan, as we speak.

79
00:04:32,439 --> 00:04:34,107
I am in Japan as well.

80
00:04:34,858 --> 00:04:36,777
Then we'll be quite close to each other.

81
00:04:36,902 --> 00:04:40,113
Who knows? We might even
have the chance to meet face to face.

82
00:04:40,572 --> 00:04:41,740
I hope so.

83
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:45,327
[Near] Well, that'll be something
to look forward to.

84
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:46,620
[Light] Yes.

85
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:49,831
[Near] When that time comes, we'll finish
this Kira matter once and for all.

86
00:04:50,207 --> 00:04:51,374
[Light] Definitely.

87
00:04:54,753 --> 00:04:56,546
It's all becoming clear to me.

88
00:04:57,005 --> 00:05:00,842
From the very beginning and even now,
it's been a one-on-one fight against L.

89
00:05:01,343 --> 00:05:02,928
And even though he's dead,

90
00:05:03,178 --> 00:05:05,305
the battle's just shifted to his heirs.

91
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:07,474
Very well, Near.

92
00:05:07,599 --> 00:05:09,643
Fine, I'll come out to play if you will.

93
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,311
It's only fair, after all.

94
00:05:12,229 --> 00:05:13,522
And when we meet,

95
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:16,650
we'll find out which of us
is truly prepared to win

96
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:18,610
and whose wits will prevail.

97
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:22,113
When that happens,
this long battle will end

98
00:05:22,531 --> 00:05:25,242
and I can finally begin
my reign at the top!

99
00:05:27,577 --> 00:05:30,038
[Near] First, let's review
what we know so far.

100
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:32,415
L is Light Yagami...

101
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:34,793
and he's also Kira.

102
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:37,754
For now, we'll call him L-Kira.

103
00:05:38,338 --> 00:05:39,923
There's also another one.

104
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:42,425
Someone who has the notebook
and is currently using it.

105
00:05:42,551 --> 00:05:44,386
We'll call him X-Kira.

106
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,180
Judging by the pattern
of X-Kira's killings,

107
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:50,392
he has definitely made the deal
and acquired the Shinigami eyes.

108
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,395
L-Kira and X-Kira
can't communicate directly.

109
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:56,731
They must be planning to communicate
using Takada as a go-between.

110
00:05:57,482 --> 00:06:02,904
So, given the situation as it now stands,
there are two ways to win against Kira.

111
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:05,407
One, the simple way.

112
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:11,246
We arrange to kill both L-Kira and X-Kira
and confiscate the notebook.

113
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:15,166
However, no matter what might happen,
we will never resort to that.

114
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,585
Why not?

115
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:18,962
[Near] That's not the way we work,
Commander.

116
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:20,547
"We," sir?

117
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:22,340
Yes, that's right.

118
00:06:22,632 --> 00:06:24,634
We kill those two and the murders stop.

119
00:06:24,759 --> 00:06:27,888
Such ex post facto justification
will not be tolerated.

120
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:30,599
That's not the way L and I do things.

121
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:33,059
Because that would be an insult.

122
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:37,689
Don't forget, L entrusted this case
to those who came after him.

123
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,942
[sounds of traffic]

124
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:47,616
[car engine revving]

125
00:06:52,662 --> 00:06:55,248
So, Kiyomi, I heard on the news
the other day

126
00:06:55,332 --> 00:06:57,792
that you receive an enormous amount
of fan mail every day.

127
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:02,339
[Kiyomi] Yes. I'm told, on average,
it's about two hundred letters a day.

128
00:07:02,923 --> 00:07:05,842
[Light] Two hundred letters?
Wow, I'm a little jealous.

129
00:07:06,009 --> 00:07:10,263
Man, this is kind of boring listening
to audio only without any video feed.

130
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:14,768
I think you should look through them,
even if they are just letters from fans.

131
00:07:15,727 --> 00:07:16,770
You're right.

132
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:21,149
[Light] "Keep calm as you read this note
and the ones that follow.

133
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:23,610
Make sure not to let the people
listening to this conversation

134
00:07:23,735 --> 00:07:24,778
hear your reactions."

135
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:26,321
Huh?

136
00:07:28,448 --> 00:07:30,659
[Light] The SPK has started
to make its move.

137
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:32,827
You have to start thinking
about your safety.

138
00:07:32,953 --> 00:07:35,497
Instead of only accepting messages
from Kira,

139
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:39,584
maybe you should consider making
a few demands of your own.

140
00:07:40,043 --> 00:07:42,045
Uh, Light's getting down to business.

141
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:44,547
[Light] You shouldn't only be
a spokesperson.

142
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:46,299
Your voice should be heard as well.

143
00:07:47,008 --> 00:07:48,301
Reach out to Kira.

144
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:50,345
Tell him what you think he needs to know.

145
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,727
[Light] "I have a different job for T.

146
00:07:57,978 --> 00:08:01,064
In order to create the perfect world
that Kira has envisioned,

147
00:08:01,231 --> 00:08:05,235
I want you to begin judging
and punishing people as Kira."

148
00:08:05,443 --> 00:08:06,528
[gasps]

149
00:08:08,780 --> 00:08:10,240
It's all right, Kiyomi.

150
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:13,159
I have faith in you. It's gonna be okay.

151
00:08:14,285 --> 00:08:18,039
If you can do this, I'm sure
you'll be able to send Kira information

152
00:08:18,331 --> 00:08:20,417
that you don't want the SPK to know about.

153
00:08:25,338 --> 00:08:27,257
[Kiyomi] All right. I'll do it.

154
00:08:28,341 --> 00:08:31,553
-We nailed it.
-That's our Light for you. He's good.

155
00:08:35,765 --> 00:08:37,851
[Teru] Delete, delete…

156
00:08:38,268 --> 00:08:39,269
Delete.

157
00:08:39,394 --> 00:08:41,521
-[phone ringing]
-Hmm?

158
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:42,981
[Teru] Kiyomi Takada?

159
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:45,775
[phone continues ringing]

160
00:08:46,818 --> 00:08:47,819
Yes?

161
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:49,779
I have an important message for you.

162
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:53,533
You are to send me a fan letter
that I'll be able to recognize as yours.

163
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:55,994
You will also enclose something else
in the envelope.

164
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:58,163
Five blank pages from the notebook.

165
00:08:59,748 --> 00:09:01,958
Carry on with your judgments
and killings as usual

166
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:04,044
until I receive the letter and the pages.

167
00:09:04,586 --> 00:09:06,171
And how about after you receive them?

168
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:08,923
You have to stop using the real notebook.

169
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:11,968
However, you must continue entering names
in a fake notebook.

170
00:09:12,302 --> 00:09:14,054
-A fake?
-That's right.

171
00:09:14,846 --> 00:09:17,640
Make a notebook that looks
as close to the original as possible

172
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:20,894
and act as if you're killing people
by using this decoy.

173
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:24,230
I understand.

174
00:09:24,689 --> 00:09:25,774
[Teru hangs up]

175
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,568
God, what are you planning?

176
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,571
No, it's not my place to question God.

177
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:33,239
His will is absolute.

178
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:37,827
My job is to do what God wishes.

179
00:09:38,036 --> 00:09:41,831
[dramatic music playing]

180
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:03,603
[upbeat theme music]

181
00:10:05,772 --> 00:10:07,524
Huh? What's this?

182
00:10:07,899 --> 00:10:09,943
It's the replacement for Kira's Kingdom.

183
00:10:10,026 --> 00:10:11,861
God, what's wrong with these people?

184
00:10:12,487 --> 00:10:13,822
[TV host] Welcome to the show.

185
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:17,033
Today, Ms. Takada will introduce
her four new female bodyguards

186
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:19,994
who were selected after
a rigorous screening process.

187
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:23,289
The first is the winner
of the 22nd World Karate Championships,

188
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:24,833
Ms. Tatsumi Ooyama.

189
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:29,212
The second is a former CIA agent,
Ms. Hal Lidner.

190
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:32,674
[Light] If there's an SPK member
among these bodyguards,

191
00:10:32,757 --> 00:10:34,467
it would have to be Hal Lidner.

192
00:10:34,884 --> 00:10:38,138
Looks like Near's conducting
his own investigation of Takada.

193
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:40,765
[reporter] A phantom killer
who stabbed six people

194
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:42,267
in Shinjuku's busy quarters...

195
00:10:42,350 --> 00:10:44,811
[Near] Who would I choose
to be X-Kira...

196
00:10:45,562 --> 00:10:47,772
out of all the people in the world?

197
00:10:48,273 --> 00:10:51,025
[Kiyomi on TV] Educating our children
about the existence of Kira

198
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:53,862
and the meaning of his teachings
must be made mandatory.

199
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:57,031
Above all, we must teach our children
that Kira is good.

200
00:10:57,532 --> 00:11:01,161
[Near] Takada was chosen
because she's a strong supporter of Kira.

201
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,537
So...

202
00:11:03,621 --> 00:11:07,959
that means X-Kira must be someone who knew
that Takada was a Kira-worshipper,

203
00:11:08,501 --> 00:11:11,254
someone who had a close,
intimate relationship with her

204
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:12,463
before selection.

205
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:16,342
Also, Kira will not forgive any crime,
no matter how small.

206
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:18,219
From this point onwards,

207
00:11:18,386 --> 00:11:20,847
you should assume that any person alive
is a viable target.

208
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:25,143
[tense, dramatic music playing]

209
00:11:33,985 --> 00:11:35,653
I'd like to hear Kira's voice.

210
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,281
I want to hear his thoughts once again.

211
00:11:39,073 --> 00:11:42,368
We should follow his teachings,
exactly as Kira ordered.

212
00:11:42,619 --> 00:11:45,872
To me, it's obviously the quickest path
to lasting world peace.

213
00:11:45,997 --> 00:11:47,624
THINKING ABOUT THE RECONSTRUCTION OF JAPAN

214
00:11:47,707 --> 00:11:50,627
Youth have a responsibility.
I think it is of the utmost importance

215
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:52,629
that young people do all they can
to contribute.

216
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:54,464
It's our duty to improve our society.

217
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:58,426
If there are no words or orders from Kira,
then we have only one choice.

218
00:11:58,593 --> 00:12:00,553
We need to think for ourselves.

219
00:12:00,678 --> 00:12:02,513
We need to consider
what Kira has taught us,

220
00:12:02,722 --> 00:12:06,226
determine what he wants most
and make our own decisions from there.

221
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:08,436
[Near] L-Kira is Light Yagami.

222
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,189
Could X-Kira be Teru Mikami?

223
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:15,652
[voices] Kira's Kingdom... Spokesperson...

224
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:18,613
[dramatic music playing]

225
00:12:19,322 --> 00:12:22,033
Everything seems to fit into place.

226
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:24,869
[Misa] That's what I've been asking.

227
00:12:25,411 --> 00:12:27,747
So, tell me why I'm not the headliner.

228
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,041
You said I was supposed to be
the highlight

229
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:31,668
of the East-West Pop Music Festival.

230
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:33,378
Well, it's true that you're the highlight.

231
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:37,548
But when it comes to the headliner,
it's a little harder to secure that spot.

232
00:12:38,508 --> 00:12:39,425
Huh?

233
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,135
[frustrated grunt]

234
00:12:41,678 --> 00:12:44,013
[woman] That's why we should be
taking precautions.

235
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:49,394
Kiyomi Takada.

236
00:12:50,103 --> 00:12:51,229
What an idiot!

237
00:12:51,354 --> 00:12:54,565
She doesn't even realize that Light's
just using her for his investigation.

238
00:12:54,774 --> 00:12:57,527
Don't say that. You might end up dead
if she hears you.

239
00:12:57,652 --> 00:13:00,280
Duh, I know that.
That's why I whispered it quietly.

240
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:01,906
[chuckles]

241
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:03,283
[Misa gasps] Hey!

242
00:13:04,075 --> 00:13:05,451
She snickered at me!

243
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:07,954
I'm going to go kick her!

244
00:13:08,162 --> 00:13:09,330
Oh, hang on!

245
00:13:11,207 --> 00:13:13,209
[Misa squeals]

246
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:16,254
What were you trying to do?

247
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:19,132
What was I doing? What about you?

248
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:20,174
[groans]

249
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:23,845
[frustrated grunt]

250
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:28,016
Lidner, that young lady
is actually a very good friend of mine.

251
00:13:28,558 --> 00:13:30,518
Please, you shouldn't be
so rough with her.

252
00:13:30,727 --> 00:13:31,686
[scoffs]

253
00:13:31,936 --> 00:13:33,396
Of course, Miss Takada.

254
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:34,897
Please, excuse me.

255
00:13:34,981 --> 00:13:36,399
[Misa yelps]

256
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:38,651
[Mogi] Uh, Misa-Misa...

257
00:13:39,193 --> 00:13:40,403
Are you all right?

258
00:13:41,279 --> 00:13:43,865
That was so frustrating!

259
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:46,617
L, this is Near.

260
00:13:46,868 --> 00:13:48,411
I have a small request.

261
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:50,496
If Mr. Aizawa is there,

262
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:53,333
would it be possible for me
to speak to him for a moment.

263
00:13:53,458 --> 00:13:55,543
Near, this is Aizawa. What is it?

264
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:59,255
I have a question regarding surveillance
for L and Takada's meetings.

265
00:13:59,339 --> 00:14:02,550
Are you recording both audio
and video feeds of their conversations?

266
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:05,470
No, only an audio feed right now.

267
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:08,473
[Near] I see.
Only wire taps at the moment.

268
00:14:08,723 --> 00:14:09,724
How interesting.

269
00:14:10,016 --> 00:14:11,184
Thank you very much.

270
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,062
If they're only using wire taps,

271
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:17,315
then it's safe to assume
that L-Kira and X-Kira

272
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,609
have found a way to contact each other
through Takada.

273
00:14:20,068 --> 00:14:22,862
Seems like Lidner could be in more danger
than we realize.

274
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:24,572
We knew the risks getting into this.

275
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:28,493
To be blunt, what's important is
that L starts focusing his attention

276
00:14:28,576 --> 00:14:29,744
on Lidner and Takada.

277
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:33,122
In the meantime, we'll use the opportunity
to investigate Mikami further.

278
00:14:33,623 --> 00:14:34,582
Hmm.

279
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:35,917
How are things, Gevanni?

280
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:37,627
Well, about Mikami...

281
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:40,713
It's strange, it's ridiculously easy
to trail him.

282
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,423
[Gevanni] He's not trying to hide
or anything.

283
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:44,759
He's lived at the same place
the past four years.

284
00:14:44,926 --> 00:14:46,886
There's nothing unusual about him.

285
00:14:47,011 --> 00:14:50,431
He also seems to be totally dedicated
to his career as a prosecutor.

286
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:52,767
I'm beginning to think he can't be X-Kira.

287
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:56,479
No, there is a very high probability
that Mikami is X-Kira.

288
00:14:56,646 --> 00:14:57,772
Please be very careful.

289
00:14:58,439 --> 00:15:01,609
[Near] Don't enter his room yet.
Just keep watch over him for now.

290
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:02,819
[Gevanni] Gotcha.

291
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,949
[Misa] Man, how many meetings
do I need to have with NHN,

292
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:09,117
for crying out loud?

293
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:12,703
And, seriously, how many times
do these people have to tell me,

294
00:15:12,787 --> 00:15:14,539
"Be careful about what you say"?

295
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:15,706
What's with that?

296
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:18,167
[Mogi] Yes. Yes, of course.
I'll ask her right now.

297
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:21,045
Listen, Misa-Misa...

298
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:23,464
Takada would like to have dinner
with you this evening.

299
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:25,550
-Just the two of you.
-Huh?

300
00:15:26,509 --> 00:15:27,802
That Kiyomi...

301
00:15:27,969 --> 00:15:29,387
What's she up to?

302
00:15:30,638 --> 00:15:31,764
Good idea!

303
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:36,477
The music festival's MC should have dinner
with the main performer at least once.

304
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,521
Tell her, "Okay."

305
00:15:38,604 --> 00:15:39,480
[grunts]

306
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:41,357
Hello?

307
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:44,610
Miss Takada, she's accepted.

308
00:15:45,194 --> 00:15:47,155
Great. I'm looking forward to it.

309
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:48,865
Oh, and Lidner?

310
00:15:49,031 --> 00:15:51,075
Please book a nice private room for us.

311
00:15:51,451 --> 00:15:54,287
And, also, I'd like you
to attend the dinner as well.

312
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:55,329
[gasps]

313
00:15:55,538 --> 00:15:56,581
Yes...

314
00:15:57,540 --> 00:16:01,335
[Christmas choir singing]

315
00:16:17,768 --> 00:16:21,522
[Kiyomi] Misa, I'm sorry to have
to invite you to dinner so late at night.

316
00:16:21,731 --> 00:16:25,193
I'm afraid it had to wait until after
the nine o'clock news was finished.

317
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:27,361
[Misa] No problem. I don't mind at all.

318
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:28,863
I'm a night owl anyway.

319
00:16:31,449 --> 00:16:33,993
[Misa gulping wine]

320
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:40,374
Well, what is it?

321
00:16:40,917 --> 00:16:43,294
I'm not really sure how to answer
a question like that.

322
00:16:44,003 --> 00:16:46,088
So, Light must be pretty busy.

323
00:16:46,506 --> 00:16:47,507
How do you two manage?

324
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:48,758
[gasps]

325
00:16:48,925 --> 00:16:50,051
Why you...

326
00:16:50,218 --> 00:16:53,846
She knows that I can't see him that much,
while she can be with him all the time!

327
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:55,056
How dare she?

328
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,767
Things are great between us.

329
00:16:57,934 --> 00:17:00,686
Light is way more affectionate
than he looks, at least with me.

330
00:17:00,811 --> 00:17:02,355
In fact, he starts clinging to me

331
00:17:02,438 --> 00:17:04,357
as soon as he gets in the door
every night.

332
00:17:04,649 --> 00:17:05,858
Ah, I see.

333
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:08,819
It sounds like you're doing well.
Thank goodness.

334
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:14,408
Yes. Actually, I should probably tell you,
since you are the MC...

335
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:18,829
I'm going to announce my engagement
to Light at the Pop Music Festival.

336
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,585
Does he know about this?

337
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:27,755
Of course, he does. It's an engagement.

338
00:17:27,838 --> 00:17:30,258
It's not as if I can get engaged
to myself!

339
00:17:30,466 --> 00:17:32,260
He proposed to me more than a month ago.

340
00:17:32,343 --> 00:17:33,636
It was so romantic.

341
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:35,888
Don't you think it'd be exciting
to announce it

342
00:17:35,972 --> 00:17:38,266
at the Pop Music Festival, Miss MC?

343
00:17:46,941 --> 00:17:47,817
Why not?

344
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:49,944
If you're able to, that is.

345
00:17:50,319 --> 00:17:52,238
What do you mean, "if I'm able to"?

346
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:54,448
What? Are you not going to let me
announce it?

347
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:56,033
Or maybe it's something else.

348
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:59,036
Maybe you're gonna get Kira to kill me.

349
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:02,748
Of course not.

350
00:18:02,999 --> 00:18:05,501
Only Kira can decide
who he's going to punish.

351
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:08,170
I have nothing to do with his decisions.

352
00:18:08,379 --> 00:18:11,173
Besides, I've always thought of you
as a good friend, Misa.

353
00:18:11,299 --> 00:18:13,301
You shouldn't say such terrible things.

354
00:18:13,593 --> 00:18:16,387
Anyway, I don't have any intention
of killing anyone,

355
00:18:16,554 --> 00:18:18,639
no matter how horrible they might be.

356
00:18:18,848 --> 00:18:19,974
[grunts in frustration]

357
00:18:20,850 --> 00:18:22,059
Well, whatever.

358
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,353
I used to really like Kira too, you know.

359
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:27,398
But I know for sure
that Light's gonna catch him soon.

360
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:30,234
[Misa gulps noisily]

361
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:32,069
[exhales] Yeah...

362
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:35,323
Once he gets caught,
it'll be nothing but bad news for him.

363
00:18:35,865 --> 00:18:37,950
And as for you, you'll probably be...

364
00:18:38,326 --> 00:18:39,201
executed.

365
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:41,078
[Kiyomi gasps]

366
00:18:42,580 --> 00:18:43,706
Miss Takada!

367
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:45,166
Are you all right?

368
00:18:45,583 --> 00:18:46,500
Huh?

369
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:50,212
[Kiyomi chuckles]

370
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:57,094
Listen, Kiyomi. I am the real Kira.

371
00:18:57,928 --> 00:18:59,722
Please, join me, Kiyomi...

372
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:02,808
and you will be
the goddess of the new world.

373
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:10,191
-[Kiyomi] Miss Amane?
-Yes?

374
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:12,318
I find this unpleasant.

375
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:15,279
[huffs] Oh yeah? I feel the same!

376
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:17,823
Obviously this was a bad idea.

377
00:19:18,032 --> 00:19:20,660
I should've waited until you grew up
and learned a few manners

378
00:19:20,785 --> 00:19:22,078
before I invited you to dinner.

379
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:23,746
I suppose I'll know better next time.

380
00:19:23,871 --> 00:19:25,289
-Goodbye.
-Oh...

381
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:27,416
I'm older than you, Kiyomi.

382
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,626
And, anyways...

383
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:31,545
you're being childish for storming out
in the middle of dinner

384
00:19:31,629 --> 00:19:33,422
over a silly little comment.

385
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:35,341
[Misa laughs loudly]

386
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:37,885
[door opening]

387
00:19:41,472 --> 00:19:47,144
[classical music playing]

388
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,524
[Misa] Hey, Mochi!

389
00:19:51,774 --> 00:19:54,568
Thanks for waiting, Mochi! How are you?

390
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,030
[Mogi] Are you okay?

391
00:19:58,155 --> 00:20:01,325
[Misa] Of course, I am. I won, after all!

392
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:04,203
-Won?
-Yeah. It was easy!

393
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:05,496
[Misa giggles]

394
00:20:06,247 --> 00:20:08,833
About tonight's meeting
between Takada and Amane,

395
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,001
they just talked about Light Yagami.

396
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:12,837
If you read between the lines,

397
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:15,089
they were arguing over
which one was his lover.

398
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:16,882
Your thoughts?

399
00:20:16,966 --> 00:20:18,592
All I can determine is this.

400
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:21,929
Light Yagami is popular with the ladies.

401
00:20:22,471 --> 00:20:25,599
And we know that Takada and Amane
both adore him.

402
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:27,768
Near, please be serious about this!

403
00:20:27,852 --> 00:20:30,229
[Near] It is serious if they're both
truly in love with him.

404
00:20:30,771 --> 00:20:32,606
They will not easily betray him.

405
00:20:33,149 --> 00:20:35,901
In fact, they'll likely do
whatever he asks.

406
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:40,072
[train thundering past]

407
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:48,789
[woman] Please stop!

408
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:50,875
Come on now, lady.

409
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,711
I mean, wearing a short skirt like that
in the winter?

410
00:20:54,003 --> 00:20:55,296
It's an invitation.

411
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:56,797
Please, someone!

412
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:00,426
Hmm?

413
00:21:02,178 --> 00:21:03,304
A cell phone?

414
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:06,307
[gasps]

415
00:21:06,599 --> 00:21:08,309
[Gevanni] Mikami's just taken out
a notebook.

416
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:11,854
[wheels grinding]

417
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:13,606
Delete…

418
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,484
He's writing something in it.
Could that be it?

419
00:21:17,568 --> 00:21:18,861
[Gevanni] He's getting off the train.

420
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:20,988
[woman screaming]

421
00:21:22,364 --> 00:21:23,783
[woman sobbing]

422
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:30,080
[suspenseful music playing]

423
00:21:30,164 --> 00:21:37,087
TO BE CONTINUED

424
00:21:42,051 --> 00:21:47,723
[theme music playing]
